  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Young people learn about Rights at Work</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The idea of the project is to use the gamification of the Rights@Work package in schools and in other contexts to raise young people&apos;s awareness of their rights at work. This would include important guidance on how to avoid the traps of the informal economy, understand their rights and obligations at work, know about where they can obtain support and increase their participation in the governance of the labour market, including in the case young people decide to follow through on the declared intention to migrate (as it emerges in the 2017 Labour Force Survey, as the main cause for not being active on the labour market).</narrative>
  </description>
